Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.00,0:01:59.00,名单,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,600)}压制：{\c&H280D9C&}beloved     {\c&HE0DBD1&}时间轴：{\c&H280D9C&}阿黎     {\c&HE0DBD1&}总监：{\c&H280D9C&}络睿 金刚妹
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.96,0:00:06.22,中文,,0,0,0,,上集回顾\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Previously...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.29,0:00:07.45,中文,,0,0,0,,我的丈夫\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}My husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.45,0:00:08.96,中文,,0,0,0,,无论你做什么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Nothing you could ever do
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.06,0:00:10.35,中文,,0,0,0,,都阻挡不了我对你的爱\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}could stop my loving you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.62,0:00:11.31,中文,,0,0,0,,乔纳森\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Jonathan,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.32,0:00:13.41,中文,,0,0,0,,乔纳森 韦克菲尔德 兰德尔 终于找到了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Jonathan Wolverton Randall, finally.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.41,0:00:16.84,中文,,0,0,0,,是不列颠军队的重骑兵上尉\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Captain of Dragoons in the British Army,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.84,0:00:19.02,中文,,0,0,0,,还是你的直系祖先\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}and your direct ancestor.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.47,0:00:21.36,中文,,0,0,0,,也叫黑杰克\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Otherwise known as Black Jack.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.87,0:00:24.95,中文,,0,0,0,,我听说过克雷尼顿这个地方的故事\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I heard stories of a place called Craigh Na Dun.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.42,0:00:28.71,中文,,0,0,0,,我已经不是在20世纪了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I was no longer in the 20th century.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.78,0:00:31.42,中文,,0,0,0,,弗兰克都经历了些什么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}What was Frank going through?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.07,0:00:32.85,中文,,0,0,0,,克莱尔\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Claire?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.06,0:00:35.75,中文,,0,0,0,,也许我被绑架了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Perhaps I was abducted.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.83,0:00:39.20,中文,,0,0,0,,也许我死去了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Perhaps I was dead...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.81,0:00:44.28,中文,,0,0,0,,或者也许 最糟糕的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Or perhaps, worst of all,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.85,0:00:48.63,中文,,0,0,0,,我离开了他 跟随了另一个男人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I had left him for another man.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.98,0:02:37.88,中文,,0,0,0,,我是因弗尼斯警局的博伊尔巡警\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Inverness police, Constable Boyle speaking,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.88,0:02:38.90,中文,,0,0,0,,我能为你效劳吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}how may I help you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.13,0:02:42.83,中文,,0,0,0,,知道了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.62,0:02:44.81,中文,,0,0,0,,是的 女士 我知道了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Yes, ma'am, I see now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.81,0:02:47.10,中文,,0,0,0,,你第一次发现东西丢了 是什么时候\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}When did you first notice the items were missing?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.75,0:02:52.58,中文,,0,0,0,,他回来了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}He's back.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.98,0:02:56.21,中文,,0,0,0,,我的上帝圣母娘娘啊\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Jesus, Mary, and Joseph.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.18,0:02:59.56,中文,,0,0,0,,时辰到了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I think today's the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.14,0:03:00.85,中文,,0,0,0,,就今天吗 先生\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Today, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.85,0:03:02.83,中文,,0,0,0,,我已经拖太久了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I have let this go on long enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.44,0:03:05.18,中文,,0,0,0,,就今天 中士\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Today, Sergeant.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.57,0:03:17.32,中文,,0,0,0,,祝你好运\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Good luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.76,0:03:20.38,中文,,0,0,0,,是的女士 你说的我都听到了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Yes, ma'am, I heard every word you said.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.38,0:03:22.50,中文,,0,0,0,,我们会马上派人过去的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I'm gonna send a man over straightaway.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.77,0:03:34.50,中文,,0,0,0,,抱歉 兰德尔先生 你知道的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I am sorry, Mr. Randall, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.29,0:03:36.57,中文,,0,0,0,,非常非常抱歉\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I'm very, very sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.83,0:03:39.78,中文,,0,0,0,,我真希望我们能帮上忙\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Please believe me when I say
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.79,0:03:42.36,中文,,0,0,0,,请你相信我的话\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I wish there was more that we could do.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.99,0:03:43.95,中文,,0,0,0,,当然 你还有自己的事儿\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Well, there's your job,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.52,0:03:46.83,中文,,0,0,0,,不过也许你能做到\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}perhaps you could do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.86,0:03:51.95,中文,,0,0,0,,我知道你肯定很失望\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I know this must be disappointing to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.07,0:03:53.13,中文,,0,0,0,,失望\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Disappointing?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.28,0:03:55.43,中文,,0,0,0,,真是个有趣的词儿\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}That's an interesting word.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.87,0:03:59.89,中文,,0,0,0,,意思就是期望没有达到\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}It suggests expectations that were unmet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.46,0:04:03.67,中文,,0,0,0,,不过我对你们部门的期望\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}My expectations of your department were...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.38,0:04:05.62,中文,,0,0,0,,一开始就不高\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}were low to begin with,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.62,0:04:06.84,中文,,0,0,0,,而且我可以确信的是\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}and I can assure you
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.44,0:04:10.02,中文,,0,0,0,,这点儿期望你们倒是屡次达到了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}that you have met those expectations at every turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.91,0:04:15.95,中文,,0,0,0,,过去整整六个星期\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}We have spent the past six weeks
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.95,0:04:18.50,中文,,0,0,0,,我们搜遍了100平方英里的崎岖地带\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}searching over 100 square miles of rugged terrain,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.06,0:04:21.90,中文,,0,0,0,,实施了175次走访 投入了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}conducted 175 interviews, invest-
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.90,0:04:23.59,中文,,0,0,0,,投入了超过1000个小时的人力时间\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Invested over 1,000 man hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.59,0:04:25.76,中文,,0,0,0,,我知道这些陈词滥调 警官 但你告诉我\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I know the litany, Detective, but tell me,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.76,0:04:28.16,中文,,0,0,0,,你说进行了这么多努力\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}what do you have to show for these
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.16,0:04:29.15,中文,,0,0,0,,想表达什么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}for these efforts?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.98,0:04:34.98,中文,,0,0,0,,我妻子不见了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}My wife has disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.53,0:04:41.06,中文,,0,0,0,,对于她到底发生了什么事情\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Do you have any idea at all
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.02,0:04:43.35,中文,,0,0,0,,你们有没有一点点线索\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}what might have happened to her?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.43,0:04:47.96,中文,,0,0,0,,我们根本没找到尸体\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}We haven't found a body.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.67,0:04:50.85,中文,,0,0,0,,这说明她很可能还活着\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Now, that tells me that she's probably still alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.85,0:04:53.18,中文,,0,0,0,,车里没有血迹 也没有搏斗过的痕迹\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}No blood in the car, no sign of a struggle,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.33,0:04:54.58,中文,,0,0,0,,这说明\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}now, that tells me that
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.85,0:04:58.36,中文,,0,0,0,,她很可能不是被强行带走的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}she probably wasn't taken against her will.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.36,0:05:00.71,中文,,0,0,0,,是啊 你们最喜欢这种解释了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Yeah, your favorite theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.50,0:05:05.68,中文,,0,0,0,,你说你在她不见的前一个晚上\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You personally witnessed a man staring up at her window
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.68,0:05:07.15,中文,,0,0,0,,看到一个男人盯着她的窗户看\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}the night before she disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.15,0:05:08.67,中文,,0,0,0,,我从一开始就说\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I have said from the very beginning
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.33,0:05:11.60,中文,,0,0,0,,那个高地人肯定和这件事有关\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}that the highlander is certainly involved in some way.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.60,0:05:14.48,中文,,0,0,0,,他当然有关 你这个傻瓜\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Of course he's involved, you fool.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.75,0:05:17.97,中文,,0,0,0,,他是她的情夫 他们俩私奔了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}He's her lover, and the two of them left together.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.09,0:05:20.43,中文,,0,0,0,,我的妻子没有和别的男人在一起\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}My wife is not with another man.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.58,0:05:47.68,中文,,0,0,0,,问你个问题\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Ask you a question?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.50,0:05:50.36,中文,,0,0,0,,说吧\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.94,0:05:57.28,中文,,0,0,0,,好吧 我的问题是 我不希望\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Well, my question, I don't wish to, that is...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.80,0:06:00.46,中文,,0,0,0,,我不是说想暗示\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I don't mean to imply that you have some
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.66,0:06:03.48,中文,,0,0,0,,你对男人非常了解\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}vast knowledge of men,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.48,0:06:06.58,中文,,0,0,0,,不过 在这件事上 你了解的确实比我多\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}but well, you know more than I do in such matters.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.58,0:06:07.64,中文,,0,0,0,,你直接说好了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Out with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.06,0:06:14.04,中文,,0,0,0,,那种感觉\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Is it usual,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.62,0:06:18.64,中文,,0,0,0,,当我们同枕而眠 当我们肌肤相亲时的感觉\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}what it is between us when I touch you,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.28,0:06:22.87,中文,,0,0,0,,是正常的吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}when you lie with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.53,0:06:28.46,中文,,0,0,0,,当一个男人和一个女人在一起时 都会有这种感觉吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Is it always so between a man and a woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.05,0:06:38.38,中文,,0,0,0,,就像现在这样 这种感觉\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}It's often something like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.40,0:06:49.55,中文,,0,0,0,,好吧 其实不正常\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}No, this isn't usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.50,0:06:53.47,中文,,0,0,0,,很特别的感觉\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}It's different.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.15,0:07:08.06,中文,,0,0,0,,别动\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Don't move.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.13,0:07:30.19,中文,,0,0,0,,是你的朋友吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Friend of yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.19,0:07:33.43,中文,,0,0,0,,是的 休 休 芒罗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Ay, Hugh, Hugh Munro.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.04,0:07:40.24,中文,,0,0,0,,你怎么知道我在这儿\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}How'd you know I was here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.22,0:07:49.06,中文,,0,0,0,,好吧 你看到杜戈尔和其他人在饮马\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Aye, saw Dougal and the others watering the horses?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.06,0:07:49.65,中文,,0,0,0,,好的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Aye.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.66,0:07:50.92,中文,,0,0,0,,猜到我一定在这上面\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Figured I must be up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.69,0:07:57.16,中文,,0,0,0,,她 克莱尔 我老婆\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Her. Claire, my wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.41,0:08:02.13,中文,,0,0,0,,我们就在前两天结的婚\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Married but these two days.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.83,0:08:11.83,中文,,0,0,0,,啊 他说他有消息告诉我\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Ah, says he's got news,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.83,0:08:14.56,中文,,0,0,0,,不过要先和我们喝上两杯\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}but insists we drink to you first.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.54,0:08:16.83,中文,,0,0,0,,我怎么可能拒绝\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Canna say I disagree.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.35,0:08:33.04,中文,,0,0,0,,好的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.11,0:08:35.05,中文,,0,0,0,,新婚礼物\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Wedding gift.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.61,0:08:37.65,中文,,0,0,0,,噢 你真客气\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Oh, how kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.52,0:08:44.91,中文,,0,0,0,,好漂亮\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}This is beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.44,0:08:46.78,中文,,0,0,0,,是只蜻蜓\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}It's a dragonfly.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.63,0:08:49.43,中文,,0,0,0,,谢谢你\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.28,0:08:52.49,中文,,0,0,0,,非得搞得这么正式\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Gone official, have you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.48,0:08:55.76,中文,,0,0,0,,你戴这玩意儿是不是因为最近没有比赛了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Or are these just for when the game is scarce?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.77,0:08:58.73,中文,,0,0,0,,是什么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}What are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.07,0:09:00.74,中文,,0,0,0,,乞丐铭牌\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Gaberlunzie tokens.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.51,0:09:03.64,中文,,0,0,0,,是英格兰人行乞的许可证\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}They're licenses to beg, sassenach.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.91,0:09:06.36,中文,,0,0,0,,他们只在某个特定的教区才有效\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}They're good within the borders of a single parish.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.97,0:09:08.35,中文,,0,0,0,,特定的教区\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Single parish?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.09,0:09:10.95,中文,,0,0,0,,我数了数你有一打许可证呀\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}About a dozen by my count.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.21,0:09:13.09,中文,,0,0,0,,是的 好吧\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Aye, well,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.09,0:09:15.03,中文,,0,0,0,,芒罗很特殊 你要知道\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Munro's a special case, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.99,0:09:17.92,中文,,0,0,0,,他在海上被土耳其人抓走\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}He was captured by the Turks at sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.40,0:09:20.89,中文,,0,0,0,,在阿尔及尔（阿尔及利亚首都）做了好多年奴隶\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Spent a good many years as a slave in Algiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.07,0:09:22.45,中文,,0,0,0,,他就是在那里没了舌头\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}That's where he lost his tongue.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.70,0:09:26.73,中文,,0,0,0,,被割掉了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Cut it out?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.05,0:09:34.93,中文,,0,0,0,,他们还往他腿上泼滚烫的油\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}And poured boiling oil on his legs.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.30,0:09:38.86,中文,,0,0,0,,他们就是这样 将一个虔诚的基督徒\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}It's how they forced captive Christians to convert
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.86,0:09:40.13,中文,,0,0,0,,变成了一个穆斯林\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}to Mussulman religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.25,0:09:52.20,中文,,0,0,0,,你说你有消息告诉我\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Said you came wi' news.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.15,0:09:59.83,中文,,0,0,0,,谁\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.20,0:10:06.07,中文,,0,0,0,,他是怎么知道的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Why would he know?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.21,0:10:11.25,中文,,0,0,0,,能信任他吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Can he be trusted?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.79,0:10:18.73,中文,,0,0,0,,他叫什么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}What's his name?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.87,0:10:23.01,中文,,0,0,0,,哈哈拉卡\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Haharack.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.46,0:10:24.29,中文,,0,0,0,,哈拉卡\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Harack?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.23,0:10:27.17,中文,,0,0,0,,哈洛克\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Horrock.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.61,0:10:30.78,中文,,0,0,0,,哈洛克斯\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Horrocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.63,0:10:36.44,中文,,0,0,0,,这位哈洛克斯想什么时候在哪儿见面\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}When and where does this Horrocks want to meet?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.50,0:10:45.36,中文,,0,0,0,,好的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.74,0:10:47.53,中文,,0,0,0,,好的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.40,0:10:54.82,中文,,0,0,0,,谢谢你 真谢谢你 休\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Thank you, thank you kindly, Hugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.32,0:11:07.30,中文,,0,0,0,,有机会可以\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}There's a chance,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.05,0:11:10.09,中文,,0,0,0,,取消对我人头的悬赏\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I can get the price lifted from my head.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.09,0:11:12.97,中文,,0,0,0,,有一个可以证明我清白的目击证人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}There's a witness who can prove my innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.95,0:11:15.10,中文,,0,0,0,,他声称\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Claims he was there
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.37,0:11:17.05,中文,,0,0,0,,当我从福特威廉那儿逃走时候 他就在场\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}during my escape from Fort William,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.65,0:11:19.51,中文,,0,0,0,,他看到了杀死中士的那个人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}saw who actually killed the sergeant.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.21,0:11:23.44,中文,,0,0,0,,不过我不确定能否相信他\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}But I'm not sure I can trust him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.78,0:11:25.07,中文,,0,0,0,,那个叫哈洛克斯的吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Is this Horrocks?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.62,0:11:28.52,中文,,0,0,0,,是的 是个英格兰逃兵\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Aye, a redcoat deserter.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.13,0:11:33.39,中文,,0,0,0,,不过终于能有机会\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}But if there's a chance I can finally go home
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.59,0:11:35.85,中文,,0,0,0,,我可以眷携佳人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}with my bride,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.32,0:11:39.55,中文,,0,0,0,,克莱尔 弗雷泽一起回归故里\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Claire Fraser, Lady of Lallybroch...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.64,0:11:59.34,中文,,0,0,0,,有没有沿芬德霍恩河找过\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}What about the Findhorn River?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.38,0:12:01.30,中文,,0,0,0,,你跟他们提过吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Did you tell them?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.33,0:12:05.02,中文,,0,0,0,,他们 额 他们不感兴趣\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}They, uh, they weren't interested.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.16,0:12:08.38,中文,,0,0,0,,这是推理啊 很好的推理\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}It's a theory, a good one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.19,0:12:10.49,中文,,0,0,0,,她离开了克雷尼顿\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}She leaves Craigh Na Dun,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.49,0:12:12.51,中文,,0,0,0,,迷了路 又回头了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}gets lost, turns back,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.83,0:12:14.69,中文,,0,0,0,,想沿着芬德霍恩河回来\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}tries to follow the Findhorn River,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.78,0:12:17.61,中文,,0,0,0,,脚下一滑 然后被河水冲走\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}takes a misstep, and then is swept away by the current,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.61,0:12:19.05,中文,,0,0,0,,一直被冲到达纳韦森林\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}all the way down to the Darnaway Forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.05,0:12:22.09,中文,,0,0,0,,达纳韦森林离找到车子的地方有20英里\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Darnaway Forest is 20 miles from where the car was found.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.09,0:12:25.18,中文,,0,0,0,,啊 河水湍急 那晚水流特别快\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Ah, the river is fast, and it was swift that night.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.94,0:12:28.38,中文,,0,0,0,,都能带着她来回一趟了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}She could've been carried twice that far.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.34,0:12:31.63,中文,,0,0,0,,关于这篇区域 这些地图画得比较含糊\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}These maps of the area, they're poor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.04,0:12:33.78,中文,,0,0,0,,也许在河流的某个弯曲处\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Looks as though there are bends in the river here
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.78,0:12:35.42,中文,,0,0,0,,她被冲到了岸上\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}where she might have made it to shore,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.64,0:12:37.51,中文,,0,0,0,,然后在这山脊中找了个地方栖身 可能\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}and then found shelter along this ridge, maybe,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.51,0:12:38.86,中文,,0,0,0,,可能找了个山洞\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}maybe in a cave.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.77,0:12:41.50,中文,,0,0,0,,于是她又累又迷茫\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}So she's tired, she's lost,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.63,0:12:42.65,中文,,0,0,0,,不知去向何处\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}she doesn't know where to turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.65,0:12:45.34,中文,,0,0,0,,所以她在洞里屈身躺下 保持温暖\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}So she hunkers down in this cave to keep warm,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.59,0:12:49.14,中文,,0,0,0,,靠鱼和青蛙为食 等待救援\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}and lives on fish and frogs while waiting to be found.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.14,0:12:51.41,中文,,0,0,0,,靠鱼和青蛙活了七个星期\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Fish and frogs for seven weeks?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.41,0:12:53.14,中文,,0,0,0,,她受过军队的生存训练\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}She relied on her army survival training.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.14,0:12:55.11,中文,,0,0,0,,她是个坚强的女人 她也很聪明 她\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}She's a strong woman. She's smart. She's-
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.11,0:12:56.43,中文,,0,0,0,,这推理只是瞎找的救命稻草而已\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}We're grasping at straws.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.43,0:12:57.91,中文,,0,0,0,,先生们\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Gentlemen...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.45,0:13:01.55,中文,,0,0,0,,- 茶点准备好了 - 还有小饼干\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}- Tea is served. - And biscuits.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.55,0:13:02.97,中文,,0,0,0,,噢 谢谢你 罗杰\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Oh, thank you, Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.69,0:13:05.93,中文,,0,0,0,,请问我能吃一块小饼干吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}May I have a biscuit, please?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.16,0:13:08.55,中文,,0,0,0,,你要吃第二块小饼干吗 好吧\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You mean another biscuit? Aye.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.55,0:13:10.85,中文,,0,0,0,,你是不是吃了我所有的小饼干啊 罗杰 威克菲尔德\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Have you been eating all my biscuits, Roger Wakefield?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.07,0:13:14.32,中文,,0,0,0,,快上楼去 准备睡觉觉\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Now, go upstairs, and get ready for bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.32,0:13:16.71,中文,,0,0,0,,我马上就上来给你念故事听\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I'll be up in a minute to read you a story.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.89,0:13:44.86,中文,,0,0,0,,我想我需要更有力的线索\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I think I need something a little stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.00,0:13:46.95,中文,,0,0,0,,我陪你一起去找吧\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Care for some company?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.95,0:13:48.89,中文,,0,0,0,,不用了 谢谢 别等我了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}No, thank you. Don't wait up.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.39,0:14:12.42,中文,,0,0,0,,你要点些什么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}What can I get you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.42,0:14:13.11,中文,,0,0,0,,什么都不需要\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.22,0:14:18.90,中文,,0,0,0,,晚安 兰德尔先生\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Evening, Mr. Randall.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.59,0:14:25.71,中文,,0,0,0,,你可以叫我莎莉 不过不是我的真名\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You can call me Sally, but that's not my real name.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.71,0:14:34.20,中文,,0,0,0,,我可以为你效劳么 莎莉\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}What can I do for you, Sally?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.46,0:14:36.76,中文,,0,0,0,,是我可以为你效劳么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}It's what I can do for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.14,0:14:51.42,中文,,0,0,0,,我知道他在哪儿\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I ken where he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.52,0:14:56.25,中文,,0,0,0,,哪里\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.63,0:14:57.44,中文,,0,0,0,,不远\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Close.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.97,0:15:00.98,中文,,0,0,0,,我带你去\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I'll take you to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.75,0:15:03.64,中文,,0,0,0,,不是现在\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Not now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.04,0:15:06.54,中文,,0,0,0,,周围耳目众多\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}There's too many eyes and ears in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.48,0:15:09.92,中文,,0,0,0,,来德拉蒙德巷找我\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Meet me on Drummond Lane,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.58,0:15:12.99,中文,,0,0,0,,十二点半的时候 你从鞋匠的店经过\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Just past the cobbler shop at half past 12:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.64,0:15:15.82,中文,,0,0,0,,你一个人来 带好报酬\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Come alone and bring the reward.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.33,0:15:19.43,中文,,0,0,0,,他和她在一起吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Is he with her?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.17,0:15:22.04,中文,,0,0,0,,我的妻子\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}My wife?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.15,0:15:24.99,中文,,0,0,0,,我不知道\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.64,0:15:28.10,中文,,0,0,0,,我能做的只是把你带到他那儿去\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}All I can do is take you to where he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.10,0:15:29.61,中文,,0,0,0,,之后就不关我的事了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}After that, it's your concern.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.80,0:15:31.40,中文,,0,0,0,,记住 十二点半\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Remember, half past 12:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.39,0:15:45.14,中文,,0,0,0,,再来一杯\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Another.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.39,0:15:45.14,中文,,0,0,0,,再来一杯\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Another.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.57,0:15:49.41,中文,,0,0,0,,于是河马带着建筑师\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}And so the waterhorse carries the builder
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.56,0:15:51.04,中文,,0,0,0,,走向水中\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}straight into the water,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.84,0:15:53.81,中文,,0,0,0,,并且沉到很深的水底\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}and down through the depths
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.81,0:15:56.75,中文,,0,0,0,,带他来到了自己冰冷还带着鱼腥味的小屋\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}to his own cold, fishy home,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.65,0:16:00.70,中文,,0,0,0,,然后他告诉建房子的人 如果他想要自由\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}then he tells the builder if he would be free,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.38,0:16:03.79,中文,,0,0,0,,必须先建一座漂亮的房子\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}he must build a fine house,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.25,0:16:06.41,中文,,0,0,0,,还要有一个烟囱\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}and a muckle chimney as well,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.82,0:16:11.33,中文,,0,0,0,,这样河马的妻子就能用火暖手\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}so that the waterhorse's wife could warm her hands
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.33,0:16:14.75,中文,,0,0,0,,还可以炸鱼\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}by the fire and fry her fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.34,0:16:22.22,中文,,0,0,0,,没有别的选择 建楼的人只好照着他的话做\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}And the builder, having little choice, did as he was bid,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.05,0:16:25.53,中文,,0,0,0,,因为河马的妻子在她的新家里\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}because the waterhorse's wife was sad,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.53,0:16:29.42,中文,,0,0,0,,感到非常难过 寒冷和饥饿\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}and cold, and hungry in her new home beneath the waves.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.68,0:16:37.19,中文,,0,0,0,,我们回到理士的时候刚好是圣诞季节\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Be yuletide by the time we get back to Leoch.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.99,0:16:42.02,中文,,0,0,0,,圣诞节\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Christmas...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.00,0:16:45.68,中文,,0,0,0,,你们肯定不会在火炉边挂长袜\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I don't suppose you hang stockings by the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.72,0:16:48.10,中文,,0,0,0,,是为了把它们烤干吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}To dry them off, you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.28,0:16:50.29,中文,,0,0,0,,当我没说\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Never mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.58,0:16:55.39,中文,,0,0,0,,后来河马的妻子感到很温暖\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}And the waterhorse's wife was warm then,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.90,0:17:00.41,中文,,0,0,0,,也很开心 家里存满了她为晚饭所准备的烤鱼\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}and happy, and full of the fish she fried for her supper,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.76,0:17:02.80,中文,,0,0,0,,但是当那个人来到\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}but when the man came down to the...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.80,0:17:03.60,中文,,0,0,0,,怎么了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.04,0:17:06.57,中文,,0,0,0,,那些马 它们很躁动\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}The horses, they're restless.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.75,0:17:08.67,中文,,0,0,0,,有人在附近\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Someone's near.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.23,0:17:13.12,中文,,0,0,0,,现在先别动 我们都感觉到了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Now, don't move. We all know.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.16,0:17:17.39,中文,,0,0,0,,消失在了阴暗的水中\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}...disappearing into the murky waters below.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.83,0:17:19.84,中文,,0,0,0,,于是加夫湖东部的水域\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}And the waters of the east end
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.28,0:17:23.35,中文,,0,0,0,,再也没有结冰过\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}of Loch Garve never freeze over,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.61,0:17:27.85,中文,,0,0,0,,因为从河马家烟囱传来的热气把冰给融化了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}because the heat from the waterhorse's chimney melts the ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.85,0:17:29.48,中文,,0,0,0,,看见那棵倒下的树了吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}See that fallen tree?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.32,0:17:32.96,中文,,0,0,0,,等会你就过去 待在那别动\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}When I say, go to it and don't move.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.71,0:17:36.63,中文,,0,0,0,,拿上这个\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Take this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.53,0:17:45.09,中文,,0,0,0,,住在水里的河马只有鱼一样的牙齿\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}The waterhorse beneath the waves has but fish's teeth
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.09,0:17:48.30,中文,,0,0,0,,只能吃到蜗牛和水草\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}and feeds on snails and water weeds
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.30,0:17:50.68,中文,,0,0,0,,和其他一些湿冷的东西\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}and cold, wet things.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.21,0:17:54.29,中文,,0,0,0,,他的血液和水一样冰冷\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}His blood runs cold as water
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.29,0:17:56.12,中文,,0,0,0,,不再需要火焰\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}and has no need of fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.12,0:17:58.25,中文,,0,0,0,,快走 注意马车\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Go! Mind the wagon!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.39,0:18:08.42,中文,,0,0,0,,给我下来\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Get off!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.95,0:18:18.91,中文,,0,0,0,,他们想要粮食和马匹\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}They're going for the grain and the horses.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.98,0:18:21.04,中文,,0,0,0,,别过来\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Stay back.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.01,0:18:50.70,中文,,0,0,0,,回来啊\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Come on, ye!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.20,0:18:53.29,中文,,0,0,0,,给我回来\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.43,0:19:02.44,中文,,0,0,0,,克莱尔\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Claire!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.17,0:19:04.51,中文,,0,0,0,,我没事\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I'm all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.60,0:19:05.96,中文,,0,0,0,,我很好\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I'm all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.28,0:19:08.80,中文,,0,0,0,,那些人是谁\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Who were those men?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.80,0:19:09.93,中文,,0,0,0,,格兰特人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}The Grants.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.28,0:19:11.74,中文,,0,0,0,,他们有抢走什么东西吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Did they take anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.81,0:19:13.51,中文,,0,0,0,,一匹马 三袋粮食\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}A horse, three bags of grain,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.51,0:19:14.59,中文,,0,0,0,,钱没被偷\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}but none of the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.59,0:19:16.67,中文,,0,0,0,,- 一匹马 - 可能更糟\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}- A horse? - Could've been worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.61,0:19:19.05,中文,,0,0,0,,- 你还好吧 威利 - 是的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}- Are you all right, Willie? - Aye.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.99,0:19:21.06,中文,,0,0,0,,看到他们逃跑的速度了吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Did you see that shot?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.06,0:19:24.04,中文,,0,0,0,,简直一溜烟儿呀\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}It was at 20 paces if it was one.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.46,0:19:59.89,中文,,0,0,0,,兰德尔先生\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Mr. Randall,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.22,0:20:02.02,中文,,0,0,0,,我还以为你不会出现了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I was starting to think you weren't gonna show.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.02,0:20:03.47,中文,,0,0,0,,我想我还没迟到\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I believe I'm on time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.47,0:20:05.21,中文,,0,0,0,,我只是以为你会早到\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I just thought you might be early.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.22,0:20:18.26,中文,,0,0,0,,这里\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.81,0:20:24.83,中文,,0,0,0,,哪里\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.95,0:20:30.55,中文,,0,0,0,,把钱交出来\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Give us the reward.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.16,0:20:48.18,中文,,0,0,0,,住手\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.80,0:20:50.46,中文,,0,0,0,,求你了 快住手\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Stop, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.39,0:20:54.89,中文,,0,0,0,,他会死掉的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You're gonna kill him!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.50,0:21:00.93,中文,,0,0,0,,不要\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}No! No! No!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.93,0:21:03.90,中文,,0,0,0,,不要\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}No! No! No!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.03,0:21:09.72,中文,,0,0,0,,这里根本就没有高地人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}There is no highlander is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.25,0:21:11.31,中文,,0,0,0,,是不是\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.31,0:21:13.73,中文,,0,0,0,,没有\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}No, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.00,0:21:23.44,中文,,0,0,0,,在这个现代社会\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}It's fashionable in this modern age
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.44,0:21:26.88,中文,,0,0,0,,大家都不再理会善恶之分\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}to dismiss the idea of good and evil,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.27,0:21:29.66,中文,,0,0,0,,但邪恶还是会存在\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}but there is evil,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.77,0:21:33.80,中文,,0,0,0,,并且它总是打好人的主意\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}and it finds purchase in good men
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.57,0:21:37.97,中文,,0,0,0,,让罪人纵享狂热带来的快感\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}by giving sin the sweet taste of ecstasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.56,0:21:41.48,中文,,0,0,0,,纳粹党喝下毒药\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}The Nazis drank from that poisoned cup,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.48,0:21:42.96,中文,,0,0,0,,还以为他们喝的只是\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}thinking all the while they were slaking
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.97,0:21:44.69,中文,,0,0,0,,美味可口的红酒\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}their thirst with the sweetest wine.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.69,0:21:46.01,中文,,0,0,0,,你的意思是\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Are you suggesting that I have
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.01,0:21:48.00,中文,,0,0,0,,我也在喝同样的酒吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}been drinking from the same cup?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.55,0:21:50.37,中文,,0,0,0,,邪恶之酒只有一杯\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Evil has but one cup.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.08,0:21:53.19,中文,,0,0,0,,他们一般会慢慢品尝\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}They drank long and deep.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.74,0:21:55.58,中文,,0,0,0,,你只不过刚尝一口\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Yours was but a sip.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.76,0:21:58.32,中文,,0,0,0,,不要再继续尝试了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Make it your last.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.63,0:22:01.64,中文,,0,0,0,,不要再让黑暗指引着你\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Turn away from the darkness that beckons you,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.64,0:22:04.18,中文,,0,0,0,,要回头走向光明\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}and go back into the light.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.58,0:22:06.52,中文,,0,0,0,,你是说让我离开因弗尼斯\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You mean leave Inverness.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.23,0:22:08.28,中文,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Aye.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.22,0:22:12.85,中文,,0,0,0,,回到牛津去\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Go back to Oxford.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.25,0:22:15.44,中文,,0,0,0,,重新开始你的生活\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You start your life over.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.32,0:22:20.80,中文,,0,0,0,,那克莱尔呢\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}And what of Caire?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.18,0:22:25.50,中文,,0,0,0,,别管她了 就像她不管你一样\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Let her go, just as she has let you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.79,0:22:34.99,中文,,0,0,0,,所以你认为她是自愿\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}So you believe that she left with the Highlander
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.99,0:22:36.67,中文,,0,0,0,,跟着高地人离开的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}of her own volition?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.83,0:22:43.89,中文,,0,0,0,,你有没有读过福尔摩斯这本书 弗兰克\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Have you ever read Sherlock Holmes, Frank?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.12,0:22:46.66,中文,,0,0,0,,写得非常好\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Marvelous books.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.20,0:22:49.85,中文,,0,0,0,,里面有提到一个观点\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}One point he makes,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.54,0:22:52.35,中文,,0,0,0,,当你排除掉所有不可能的情况\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}when you eliminate the impossible,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.35,0:22:55.12,中文,,0,0,0,,剩下的即使再不可能\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}whatever remains, however improbable,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.29,0:22:56.65,中文,,0,0,0,,也只能是真相\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}must be the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.00,0:23:14.02,中文,,0,0,0,,我不知道\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.02,0:23:16.01,中文,,0,0,0,,就从我手里不见了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}It just slipped out of my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.88,0:23:18.32,中文,,0,0,0,,找到了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.38,0:23:19.56,中文,,0,0,0,,好家伙\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Good man.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.13,0:23:29.38,中文,,0,0,0,,对我来说这又长又重\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}It's too long and heavy for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.43,0:23:31.41,中文,,0,0,0,,女人都这么跟我说的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Lasses say that to me all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.41,0:23:32.34,中文,,0,0,0,,你给她把刀\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You gave her a knife
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.34,0:23:34.54,中文,,0,0,0,,却不告诉她怎么用\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}and you didn't show her how to use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.09,0:23:37.17,中文,,0,0,0,,该找个人教教这位女士\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Someone should teach this lady how to
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.17,0:23:39.06,中文,,0,0,0,,如何保护自己不受攻击\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}defend herself against assailants.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.06,0:23:42.70,中文,,0,0,0,,没错 安格斯 你刀使得很好\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Aye, Angus, you're a good man with a blade.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.07,0:23:45.20,中文,,0,0,0,,谢谢你的好意 不过我想我不会有事的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Uh, thank you all the same, but I think I'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.21,0:23:46.90,中文,,0,0,0,,这个世界上所有人 不管男女\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Every man and woman in the world needs to know
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.90,0:23:48.73,中文,,0,0,0,,都必须学会如何保护自己 英格兰女士\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}how to defend themselves, Sassenach,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.73,0:23:50.98,中文,,0,0,0,,尤其是那些嫁给了苏格兰人的女人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Especially those married to a Fraser.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.13,0:23:54.39,中文,,0,0,0,,我已经越来越意识到这一点了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I become more aware of that every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.50,0:23:57.16,中文,,0,0,0,,- 女人得有一个斯金度 - 没错\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}- Lass needs a sgian dubh. - Aye.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.42,0:23:58.49,中文,,0,0,0,,什么东西\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}A what?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.49,0:24:00.89,中文,,0,0,0,,斯金度 隐蔽刀\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Sgian dubh, hidden dagger.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.89,0:24:02.80,中文,,0,0,0,,有些人把它们藏在袜子里\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Some people hide them in their socks,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.80,0:24:08.23,中文,,0,0,0,,不过我把它放在更私人的地方\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}but I- keep mine in a rather more private place.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.29,0:24:12.52,中文,,0,0,0,,现在 谁想要上一课\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Now then, who needs a lesson?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.45,0:24:17.01,中文,,0,0,0,,大部分情况都是往上刺\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Mostly, you want to use the underhand.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.01,0:24:20.31,中文,,0,0,0,,当你快要倒在某人身上\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Overhand is only good if you're coming down
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.31,0:24:22.48,中文,,0,0,0,,并且对方的力气非常大的时候\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}on someone else with a considerable force
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.48,0:24:24.42,中文,,0,0,0,,往下刺才会比较好\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}from above ye.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.52,0:24:27.34,中文,,0,0,0,,我还是觉得对女人来说毒药才是最好的武器\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I still say the only good weapon for a woman is poison.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.34,0:24:30.74,中文,,0,0,0,,也许吧 但打起来的时候这招可不好使\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Perhaps, but it has certain deficiencies in combat.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.87,0:24:32.92,中文,,0,0,0,,知道了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.75,0:24:36.20,中文,,0,0,0,,那我该朝哪刺下去\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}So where do I aim my sgian dubh?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.66,0:24:38.46,中文,,0,0,0,,如果你们是面对面的话\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}If you're killing face to face,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.84,0:24:39.93,中文,,0,0,0,,这里\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}here.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.82,0:24:42.64,中文,,0,0,0,,用最大的力气\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Aim straight up, and then,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.64,0:24:44.67,中文,,0,0,0,,朝着心脏笔直地刺下去\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}as hard as you can into the heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.40,0:24:47.95,中文,,0,0,0,,不 要避免刺到胸骨\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Uhoh, avoid the breast bone.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.59,0:24:52.16,中文,,0,0,0,,如果你把刀刺进这个柔软的部位的话\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You get your knife stuck in that soft part on the top,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.33,0:24:53.79,中文,,0,0,0,,你的小刀就再也派不上用场了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}you'll be without a knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.64,0:24:58.57,中文,,0,0,0,,那么 是这里\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}So... right there?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.57,0:25:00.27,中文,,0,0,0,,现在先别急着杀他 小姐\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Dinnae kill him yet, mistress.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.28,0:25:01.98,中文,,0,0,0,,等上完课先\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Wait 'til the lesson's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.56,0:25:06.89,中文,,0,0,0,,威利 过来帮个忙\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Willie, give us a hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.52,0:25:11.99,中文,,0,0,0,,转过去 我来演示一下如何从背后攻击\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Turn around, so I can show how to kill from behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.02,0:25:17.21,中文,,0,0,0,,瞄准背部的这个地方\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Now, this is the spot in the back.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.21,0:25:18.93,中文,,0,0,0,,两边都行\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Either side will do.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.94,0:25:21.40,中文,,0,0,0,,现在你知道所有的肋骨在哪了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Now, you see where all the ribs and such?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.77,0:25:24.63,中文,,0,0,0,,当你刺向背部的时候\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Very difficult to hit anything vital
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.63,0:25:26.24,中文,,0,0,0,,很难刺中要害\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}when you stab in the back.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.24,0:25:29.42,中文,,0,0,0,,刀会从肋骨间穿过\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Slip the knife between the ribs, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.42,0:25:30.80,中文,,0,0,0,,这很重要\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}That's one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.12,0:25:33.51,中文,,0,0,0,,比你想象的要难得多\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}A lot harder to do than ye might think.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.49,0:25:36.34,中文,,0,0,0,,拿着 这里\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Here, here.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.34,0:25:39.36,中文,,0,0,0,,在最后一根肋骨的下面\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Just under the last rib,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.36,0:25:40.86,中文,,0,0,0,,从下面往上\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}you stab upward...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.99,0:25:43.56,中文,,0,0,0,,刺入肾脏\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}and into the kidney.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.91,0:25:46.19,中文,,0,0,0,,直直地\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Straight up.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.34,0:25:47.71,中文,,0,0,0,,敌人就跟快石头一样倒下去了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}They'll drop like a stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.56,0:25:52.62,中文,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.23,0:25:54.65,中文,,0,0,0,,直直地\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Straight up...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.93,0:25:56.06,中文,,0,0,0,,刺进去\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}and in.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.34,0:26:02.00,中文,,0,0,0,,看 我学会了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}See, got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.01,0:27:13.86,中文,,0,0,0,,他们会不会来找我们\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Won't they come looking for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.47,0:27:15.62,中文,,0,0,0,,我跟杜戈尔说过了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I told Dougal
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.77,0:27:17.98,中文,,0,0,0,,我们还要再跟你找些草药\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}we need to find some more of your wee herbs.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.37,0:27:20.62,中文,,0,0,0,,这是我出的主意 不是吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}This is my idea, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.04,0:27:22.69,中文,,0,0,0,,他相信你了吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}And did he believe you?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.35,0:27:24.72,中文,,0,0,0,,那还用说\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Never a chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.43,0:27:33.41,中文,,0,0,0,,完全无法停止对你的渴望\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Does it ever stop, the wanting you?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.40,0:27:59.99,中文,,0,0,0,,现在我知道为什么教堂会把这称为圣礼了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Now I know why the church calls it a sacrament.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.44,0:28:02.53,中文,,0,0,0,,为什么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.87,0:28:07.86,中文,,0,0,0,,当我进入你体内的时候 感觉自己就像上帝一样\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Because I feel like god himself when I'm inside ye.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.06,0:28:10.12,中文,,0,0,0,,什么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.17,0:28:11.93,中文,,0,0,0,,是不是听起来很愚蠢\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Is that a foolish thing to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.90,0:28:14.22,中文,,0,0,0,,你在嘲笑我\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You're laughing at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.47,0:28:17.03,中文,,0,0,0,,没错 的确是的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Yes, I most certainly am.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.10,0:28:19.05,中文,,0,0,0,,那我可要给你好看\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}And you'll get what you deserve.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.35,0:28:32.35,中文,,0,0,0,,起来 你这个发情的杂种\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Get up, you rutting bastard.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.74,0:28:40.92,中文,,0,0,0,,你应该让他先弄完的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You might ha' let him finish first, 'arry.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.05,0:28:43.41,中文,,0,0,0,,中途停下来 对男人的身子可不好\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Stoppin' in the middle, now that's bad for a man's 'ealth.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.41,0:28:46.09,中文,,0,0,0,,又不是我的身子\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Oh, his 'ealth's no concern of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.33,0:28:48.67,中文,,0,0,0,,反正等会他也会没命的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}It won't be any concern of his for much longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.67,0:28:50.63,中文,,0,0,0,,把他杀了 别管他了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Well, kill him, and be done with it then,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.21,0:28:53.62,中文,,0,0,0,,现在我也来尝尝甜头\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}'cause I've a mind to take a piece o' that.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.50,0:28:59.58,中文,,0,0,0,,不\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}No...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.67,0:29:02.51,中文,,0,0,0,,我还会让你先看一阵\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}think I'll let 'im watch first.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.20,0:29:05.60,中文,,0,0,0,,喜欢吗 苏格兰杂种\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You like that, you Scottish whoreson?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.59,0:29:09.84,中文,,0,0,0,,看好了 小禽兽\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Take a good look, laddiebuck,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.84,0:29:11.09,中文,,0,0,0,,给我看仔细了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}see how it's done,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.09,0:29:13.09,中文,,0,0,0,,等会我会让这贱人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}'cause I'll have your slut moaning for more
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.09,0:29:14.16,中文,,0,0,0,,喊得更淫荡\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}before the hour is done.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.16,0:29:15.75,中文,,0,0,0,,不要\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}No!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.36,0:30:17.09,中文,,0,0,0,,我已经几周没说过话\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I have held my tongue for weeks now,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.10,0:30:18.65,中文,,0,0,0,,我再也不会当哑巴了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}and I'll be silent no longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.65,0:30:20.53,中文,,0,0,0,,你不能告诉他你的幻想\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You cannot tell him this fantasy of yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.53,0:30:23.04,中文,,0,0,0,,我知道的很清楚 我不会装傻子的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I know what I know, and I won't pretend that I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.04,0:30:24.50,中文,,0,0,0,,你所知道的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}What you know is
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.50,0:30:26.14,中文,,0,0,0,,都是一派胡言\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}a bunch of dribbledrabble and nonsense,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.14,0:30:28.31,中文,,0,0,0,,我不会把它当作真相的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}and I will not have it paraded about as fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.31,0:30:31.48,中文,,0,0,0,,他有权知道这些 并且自己决定\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}He has a right to hear it and make up his own mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.48,0:30:34.07,中文,,0,0,0,,你不能给这个可怜的人再带来虚幻的希望\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You cannot hold up false hope to the poor man,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.07,0:30:36.75,中文,,0,0,0,,他好不容易终于接受她老婆的事实\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}just as he's finally accepting that his wife...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.05,0:30:42.36,中文,,0,0,0,,这是一栋老房子\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}It's an old house.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.70,0:30:43.60,中文,,0,0,0,,好吧 那个\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}All right, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.60,0:30:46.12,中文,,0,0,0,,你是不是想跟我说什么 格雷厄姆夫人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Is there something you wish to tell me, Mrs. Graham?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.69,0:30:47.82,中文,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}There is.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.80,0:30:51.13,中文,,0,0,0,,即使这违背了我的立场\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Even if it should cost me my position,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.25,0:30:52.94,中文,,0,0,0,,但我觉得我必须把真相告诉你\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I feel I must tell you the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.94,0:30:55.68,中文,,0,0,0,,- 真相 - 至少是我知道的那部分真相\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}- The truth - The truth as I know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.52,0:31:02.98,中文,,0,0,0,,你妻子的事情 还有另外一种可能\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}There is an other explanation for what happened to your wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.76,0:31:07.72,中文,,0,0,0,,这是个古老的故事\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}The stories are old.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.29,0:31:11.23,中文,,0,0,0,,有人说和那些石头一样古老\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Some say as old as the stones themselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.56,0:31:14.04,中文,,0,0,0,,在民谣和民歌里\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}passed down from generation to generation
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.04,0:31:16.79,中文,,0,0,0,,代代相传\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}through ballads and songs.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.41,0:31:19.34,中文,,0,0,0,,我第一次是从我祖母那儿听来的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I first heard them from my grandmother,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.34,0:31:21.07,中文,,0,0,0,,她也是从她祖母那儿听来的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}and she from hers.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.47,0:31:25.30,中文,,0,0,0,,那首民歌 唱的是\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}The songs tell stories about people who...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.46,0:31:28.68,中文,,0,0,0,,人们穿越石头的故事\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}travel through the stones.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.17,0:31:30.73,中文,,0,0,0,,穿越石头\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Travel through stone?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.16,0:31:34.83,中文,,0,0,0,,我不太理解你的意思\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I'm not sure I take your meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.49,0:31:39.32,中文,,0,0,0,,倒不是说真的穿过石头本身\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Not literally through the stone itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.32,0:31:40.57,中文,,0,0,0,,就是\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You see...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.29,0:31:44.21,中文,,0,0,0,,克雷尼顿的石头圆圈\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}the circle at Craigh Na Dun marks a...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.01,0:31:46.48,中文,,0,0,0,,标志着地球上的一个地方\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}a place on the earth
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.48,0:31:48.89,中文,,0,0,0,,在那个地方 自然的力量汇聚在一起\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}where the powers of nature come together.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.89,0:31:51.45,中文,,0,0,0,,简直是迷信和胡话\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Superstition and twiddletwaddle.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.70,0:31:55.76,中文,,0,0,0,,你接着说\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.43,0:31:58.38,中文,,0,0,0,,石头采集天地之力\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}The stones gather the powers,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.38,0:32:03.00,中文,,0,0,0,,聚焦到一点 就像凸透镜一样 知道吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}and give it focus, like a glass, ye ken?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.51,0:32:05.47,中文,,0,0,0,,对特定的人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}And for certain people,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.90,0:32:08.33,中文,,0,0,0,,在特定的日子\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}on certain days,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.52,0:32:13.59,中文,,0,0,0,,石头之力会使其穿透时间的面纱\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}it allows them to pierce the veil of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.44,0:32:16.93,中文,,0,0,0,,兰德尔先生 你知道你妻子\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Mr. Randall, you know your wife
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.93,0:32:19.26,中文,,0,0,0,,不见的那天上了山\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}went up that hill the day she vanished.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.65,0:32:22.09,中文,,0,0,0,,我相信她并没有从山上下来\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I believe she didn't come back down that hill,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.09,0:32:24.80,中文,,0,0,0,,至少不是在1945年从山上下来的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}at least not in 1945.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.36,0:32:27.78,中文,,0,0,0,,我相信她穿越到了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I believe that she traveled to
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.31,0:32:30.64,中文,,0,0,0,,另外的时代里\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}some other time.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.79,0:32:42.96,中文,,0,0,0,,她会去哪里 会去哪个时代呢\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Where or... when would that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.30,0:32:44.64,中文,,0,0,0,,我不知道\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.07,0:32:47.10,中文,,0,0,0,,每个穿越者都不一样\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Every traveler is different.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.64,0:32:49.97,中文,,0,0,0,,他们必须走自己的路\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}They must make their own journey
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.33,0:32:52.23,中文,,0,0,0,,经历自己的旅程\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}on their own path,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.56,0:32:54.61,中文,,0,0,0,,不过古老的民歌里确实有说\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}but the songs do say
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.64,0:32:57.12,中文,,0,0,0,,穿越者们 通常又会回到这个时代来\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}that the travelers often return.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.31,0:33:01.42,中文,,0,0,0,,我知道了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.19,0:33:14.59,中文,,0,0,0,,我今天下午就回牛津\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I shall leave for Oxford this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.97,0:33:16.12,中文,,0,0,0,,你听到我说的了吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Did ye no hear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.12,0:33:18.28,中文,,0,0,0,,- 格雷厄姆夫人 - 他们通常会回来的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}- Mrs. Graham. - They often return.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.28,0:33:19.78,中文,,0,0,0,,我听到你说的了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I did hear you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.82,0:33:23.25,中文,,0,0,0,,我只是不相信你所说的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I simply do not share your beliefs.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.97,0:33:26.04,中文,,0,0,0,,原谅我\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Forgive me.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.62,0:33:43.74,中文,,0,0,0,,对不起\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.29,0:33:46.54,中文,,0,0,0,,真的对不起\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I'm so sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.91,0:33:49.05,中文,,0,0,0,,没事儿\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.64,0:33:51.05,中文,,0,0,0,,我们没事儿了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}We're all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.14,0:33:52.43,中文,,0,0,0,,都是我的错\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}My fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.38,0:33:54.88,中文,,0,0,0,,把你带来这里 没给你保暖\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}To bring you here without taking proper heat,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.88,0:33:56.06,中文,,0,0,0,,让你\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}and to let you be...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.46,0:34:00.17,中文,,0,0,0,,还无力去阻止\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}to not stop him.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.45,0:34:02.62,中文,,0,0,0,,没事儿\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.45,0:34:08.59,中文,,0,0,0,,你的手好冷\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}And here, you're so cold mo nighean donn.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.59,0:34:10.35,中文,,0,0,0,,冷得像冰一样\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Your hands are like ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.16,0:34:14.27,中文,,0,0,0,,杰米\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Jamie!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.50,0:34:19.69,中文,,0,0,0,,- 吓坏了 - 你还好吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}- It's shock. - Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.69,0:34:21.02,中文,,0,0,0,,我们听到了枪响\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}We heard a shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.95,0:34:23.48,中文,,0,0,0,,我吓坏了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I'm going into shock.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.93,0:34:24.99,中文,,0,0,0,,杰米\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Jamie.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.01,0:34:26.02,中文,,0,0,0,,带着别动\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Stay.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.46,0:34:31.99,中文,,0,0,0,,我吓坏了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I'm going into shock.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.41,0:34:33.61,中文,,0,0,0,,没事儿的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.36,0:34:39.34,中文,,0,0,0,,我脑海里万千思绪闪跃而过\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}My mind jumped and danced from thought to thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.34,0:34:42.00,中文,,0,0,0,,就像石头打水漂一样不断跳跃\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}like a stone skipping across a pond.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.53,0:34:45.97,中文,,0,0,0,,我父母 我看着死去的人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}My parents, men I'd seen die,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.79,0:34:49.41,中文,,0,0,0,,兰姆叔叔的烟味儿\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}the smell of uncle Lamb's cigarettes.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.76,0:34:52.11,中文,,0,0,0,,埃罗尔 弗林 荡着秋千\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Errol Flynn swinging on a rope,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.24,0:34:57.04,中文,,0,0,0,,握着匕首刺穿肾脏的感觉\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}the feeling of my dagger tip puncturing the kidney.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.08,0:35:03.44,中文,,0,0,0,,我知道他很担心我\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I knew he was worried about me,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.66,0:35:08.60,中文,,0,0,0,,知道他想谈刚才发生的事\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}knew he wanted to talk about what had happened,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.63,0:35:11.21,中文,,0,0,0,,可是我知道 如果我再次谈起\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}but I knew if I did,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.21,0:35:14.25,中文,,0,0,0,,如果我开始想我脆弱屈服\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}if I started giving rein to my feelings,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.39,0:35:15.92,中文,,0,0,0,,所有痛苦回忆都会向我扑面而来\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}things would pour out of me
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.92,0:35:18.36,中文,,0,0,0,,那些我想永远赶走的痛苦回忆\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}that I wanted to keep locked away forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.36,0:35:19.59,中文,,0,0,0,,只是吓坏了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}It's shock.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.03,0:35:22.14,中文,,0,0,0,,没事儿的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.48,0:35:24.72,中文,,0,0,0,,没事儿的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.74,0:35:28.05,中文,,0,0,0,,标志在这儿\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}There's letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.12,0:35:31.23,中文,,0,0,0,,从山脊那边过来的 没有骑马\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}The tracks lead back over the ridge, no horses.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.44,0:35:32.51,中文,,0,0,0,,很好\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.68,0:35:35.27,中文,,0,0,0,,你说的哈洛克斯\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Your man Horrocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.28,0:35:37.93,中文,,0,0,0,,芒罗说他就是像这两个人一样的逃兵\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Munro said he's a deserter like these.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.69,0:35:40.88,中文,,0,0,0,,休 芒罗是个好人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Hugh Munro's a good man.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.88,0:35:42.23,中文,,0,0,0,,这我不否认\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I won't deny it,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.24,0:35:44.19,中文,,0,0,0,,但违背对国王和国家的誓言的人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}but this is what becomes of a man
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.19,0:35:46.29,中文,,0,0,0,,就是这副样子\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}who breaks his oath to king and country.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.63,0:35:48.35,中文,,0,0,0,,如果你现在一个人去见哈洛克斯\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Now, you go and see Horrocks alone,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.36,0:35:50.84,中文,,0,0,0,,更像是走向圈套\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}you'll be walking into a trap, maist like.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.96,0:35:52.36,中文,,0,0,0,,他说得对 杰米\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}He's right, Jamie.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.51,0:35:54.45,中文,,0,0,0,,你非去见他不可 我理解\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You have to meet him, I understand that,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.77,0:35:57.80,中文,,0,0,0,,但要我说的话 我们带着武器和你一起去\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}but I say we all go with you with our swords in our hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.81,0:35:59.46,中文,,0,0,0,,不然的话 你索性就别去\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Otherwise, you don't go at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.41,0:36:01.50,中文,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Aye.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.68,0:36:02.24,中文,,0,0,0,,来\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.13,0:36:27.28,中文,,0,0,0,,我记不得是怎么上的马\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I don't remember getting on my horse.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.74,0:36:31.42,中文,,0,0,0,,不知道怎么一路骑过去的 甚至骑了多久都不记得了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I don't remember riding away, or even how long we rode.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.41,0:36:35.73,中文,,0,0,0,,我能回忆起的 只有我人生中那些关键的时刻\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}All I can recall of that pivotal moment in my life
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.39,0:36:39.67,中文,,0,0,0,,只有愤怒的感觉 我也不知道为什么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}was that I was angry, and I didn't know why.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.46,0:36:45.59,中文,,0,0,0,,为什么停下\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Why are we stopping?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.75,0:36:49.49,中文,,0,0,0,,你和韦利要留在这里\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You'll have to stay here with Willie.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.37,0:36:51.28,中文,,0,0,0,,什么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.59,0:36:52.66,中文,,0,0,0,,杜格尔说得对\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Dougal was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.53,0:36:56.09,中文,,0,0,0,,这可能是哈洛克斯的圈套\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Now, this man Horrocks may be setting a trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.85,0:36:58.06,中文,,0,0,0,,我不会再让你冒险了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I'll no risk you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.92,0:37:00.92,中文,,0,0,0,,有韦利在这保护你 会安全得多\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You'll be safer here with Willie to look out for ye.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.92,0:37:02.48,中文,,0,0,0,,我不想听这些\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I don't need an explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.19,0:37:04.53,中文,,0,0,0,,你带上韦利吧\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You can take Willie with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.16,0:37:06.06,中文,,0,0,0,,我能照顾好自己\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I can look after myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.06,0:37:07.68,中文,,0,0,0,,我觉得之前我已经证明过了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I think I've proven that earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.38,0:37:12.75,中文,,0,0,0,,你不需要再证明一次\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You needn't prove it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.36,0:37:18.95,中文,,0,0,0,,如果有英格兰士兵\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}If there are redcoats about,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.65,0:37:21.32,中文,,0,0,0,,他们最可能从南面过来\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}they'll likely come from the south.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.32,0:37:22.86,中文,,0,0,0,,- 我会十分小心的 - 好吧\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}- I'll keep an eye out. - Aye.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.09,0:37:25.08,中文,,0,0,0,,你就在这里\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You stay here.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.64,0:37:26.92,中文,,0,0,0,,我会回来的 我保证\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I'll be back, I promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.92,0:37:28.84,中文,,0,0,0,,你不应该做没有把握的保证\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You shouldn't make promises you can't keep.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.84,0:37:30.68,中文,,0,0,0,,这一次我可以保证 克莱尔\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}This one I will keep, Claire.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.51,0:37:33.19,中文,,0,0,0,,现在你答应我 你会待着不动\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Now, you promise me you'll stay put.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.19,0:37:35.16,中文,,0,0,0,,- 杰米 - 来了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}- Jamie. - Coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.16,0:37:36.56,中文,,0,0,0,,答应我 克莱尔\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Promise me, Claire.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.56,0:37:38.34,中文,,0,0,0,,发誓我回来的时候 你还会在这里\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Swear you'll be here when I get back.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.58,0:37:41.60,中文,,0,0,0,,好吧 我保证\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Fine, I promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.07,0:37:42.64,中文,,0,0,0,,好\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.68,0:37:46.36,中文,,0,0,0,,在那个时刻\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}In that moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.36,0:37:48.85,中文,,0,0,0,,我痛苦的原因非常清晰了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}the reason for my bitterness became clear to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.68,0:37:54.44,中文,,0,0,0,,我不是在生杰米的气 也不是在恨那两个英格兰逃兵\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I wasn't angry at Jamie or the redcoat deserters.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.41,0:37:57.40,中文,,0,0,0,,我是在生我自己的气\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I was angry at myself
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.40,0:37:59.03,中文,,0,0,0,,因为我全然忘记了我的计划\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}for forgetting about my plan to make
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.03,0:38:01.62,中文,,0,0,0,,全然忘记了要回到克雷尼顿的石头那儿去\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}my way back to the stones at Craigh Na Dun,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.62,0:38:04.56,中文,,0,0,0,,回到我自己的时代\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}my plan to return to my own time,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.56,0:38:06.61,中文,,0,0,0,,回到丈夫弗兰克的身边\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}to my husband, Frank.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.61,0:38:08.66,中文,,0,0,0,,柏林的美军总部宣布\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}U.S. Army headquarters in Berlin announced
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.66,0:38:12.06,中文,,0,0,0,,乔治巴顿二世将军 在今天过世\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}the death of General George S. Patton, Jr. Earlier today
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.06,0:38:15.86,中文,,0,0,0,,死于12天前的车祸中所受的重伤\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}from injuries he sustained in a car accident 12 days ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.86,0:38:18.58,中文,,0,0,0,,凯迪拉克75型号专车\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}...Cadillac model 75 staff car,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.58,0:38:20.01,中文,,0,0,0,,把将军送往\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}transporting the general...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.68,0:38:24.99,中文,,0,0,0,,同车的有一等兵霍雷斯 伍德林\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}as well as private first class Horace L. Woodring
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.99,0:38:27.35,中文,,0,0,0,,车子在西班牙境外与一辆卡车相撞\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}collided with a truck just outside of Spain.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.25,0:38:35.62,中文,,0,0,0,,作为一个颇具争议的人物 巴顿将军经历了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}A controversial figure, General Patton's career
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.62,0:38:38.25,中文,,0,0,0,,第一次和第二次世界大战\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}spanned both the first and second world wars,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.70,0:38:42.03,中文,,0,0,0,,现任美国第三军的指挥官\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}most recently as commander of the U.S. Third Army.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.74,0:39:18.51,中文,,0,0,0,,夫人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Mistress?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.72,0:39:21.75,中文,,0,0,0,,夫人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Mistress!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.85,0:39:23.97,中文,,0,0,0,,怎么了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.97,0:39:24.63,中文,,0,0,0,,我去解决一下个人问题\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}If you need me,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.63,0:39:26.98,中文,,0,0,0,,你有需要就请叫我\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I'll just be taking care of some personal business.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.19,0:39:30.71,中文,,0,0,0,,去50码开外的下风口\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Go at least 50 yards away and downwind.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.71,0:39:31.47,中文,,0,0,0,,是\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Aye.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.91,0:39:59.23,中文,,0,0,0,,我努力不去想那天草原上发生的事\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I tried to avoid thinking about the incident in the meadow,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.69,0:40:02.06,中文,,0,0,0,,可我的脑海里不断回闪\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}but my mind kept returning to it,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.06,0:40:03.64,中文,,0,0,0,,一遍又一遍\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}again, and again,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.20,0:40:07.60,中文,,0,0,0,,就像去碰一个碰不得的溃烂伤口\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}picking at a festering sore best left untouched.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.46,0:40:25.67,中文,,0,0,0,,突然 它就出现了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}And suddenly, there it was...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.78,0:40:28.05,中文,,0,0,0,,克雷尼顿\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Craigh Na Dun.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.19,0:40:33.91,中文,,0,0,0,,我的心里充满了迷茫和疑惑\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}My mind had been so clouded and confused,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.91,0:40:36.53,中文,,0,0,0,,我已经认不出来时的路了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I didn't recognize the road when we rode in.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.79,0:40:39.72,中文,,0,0,0,,没有弄错\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}There was no mistaking it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.08,0:40:42.44,中文,,0,0,0,,我又回来了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I was back
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.43,0:40:45.42,中文,,0,0,0,,回到了这一切开始的地方\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}to the place where it had all begun.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.16,0:40:50.20,中文,,0,0,0,,发生了太多事 发生了太多改变\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}So much had happened. So much had changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.45,0:40:54.46,中文,,0,0,0,,上次我在这里 我还是克莱尔兰德尔\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Last I was here, I was Claire Randall,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.46,0:40:55.89,中文,,0,0,0,,然后成了克莱尔毕彻姆\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}then Claire Beauchamp,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.89,0:40:57.43,中文,,0,0,0,,之后又成了克莱尔弗雷泽\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}then Claire Fraser.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.49,0:41:02.01,中文,,0,0,0,,问题是 我到底想成为谁\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}The question was... who did I want to be?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.63,0:43:04.49,中文,,0,0,0,,克莱尔\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Claire.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.22,0:43:09.20,中文,,0,0,0,,克莱尔\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Claire.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.68,0:43:17.37,中文,,0,0,0,,克莱尔\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Claire!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.17,0:43:24.52,中文,,0,0,0,,你在哪里 克莱尔\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Where are you, Claire?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.65,0:43:27.79,中文,,0,0,0,,弗兰克\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Frank!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.94,0:43:30.12,中文,,0,0,0,,克莱尔\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Claire!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.69,0:43:32.23,中文,,0,0,0,,弗兰克\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Frank,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.71,0:43:34.21,中文,,0,0,0,,等着我\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}wait for me,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.07,0:43:36.58,中文,,0,0,0,,弗兰克\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Frank!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.80,0:43:46.46,中文,,0,0,0,,克莱尔\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Claire.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.51,0:43:59.36,中文,,0,0,0,,弗兰克\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Frank!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.18,0:44:03.26,中文,,0,0,0,,不\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}No!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.41,0:44:05.71,中文,,0,0,0,,弗兰克\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Frank!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.13,0:44:10.34,中文,,0,0,0,,弗兰克\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Frank!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.19,0:44:18.05,中文,,0,0,0,,克莱尔\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Claire.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.72,0:45:07.58,中文,,0,0,0,,不用问我也知道我们会去哪里\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I knew where we were going without having to ask:
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.13,0:45:09.20,中文,,0,0,0,,福特 威廉\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Fort William.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.70,0:45:11.53,中文,,0,0,0,,四年前\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}The site of Jamie's incarceration
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.53,0:45:13.29,中文,,0,0,0,,杰米遭到监禁和鞭笞的地方\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}and flogging four years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.64,0:45:16.38,中文,,0,0,0,,如今 仍然是某人的私人领地\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}and now, still the province of a man
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.38,0:45:18.51,中文,,0,0,0,,而且很不幸地 他了解发生过的一切\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I unfortunately knew all too well.（I应该是and）
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.23,0:45:22.52,中文,,0,0,0,,不过他不知道我已经被抓了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}He would have no advance notice of my capture.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.52,0:45:25.25,中文,,0,0,0,,所以没时间安排审讯\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}No time to plan his interrogation.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.92,0:45:28.53,中文,,0,0,0,,而我 在颠簸的马车后面\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I, on the other hand, had the entire jolting journey
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.53,0:45:30.37,中文,,0,0,0,,有一路的时间来思考怎么办\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}in the back of the wagon to think.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.08,0:45:32.96,中文,,0,0,0,,这是我的优势\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}It was my one advantage.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.32,0:45:35.10,中文,,0,0,0,,我希望时间还够\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I prayed it would be enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.43,0:45:39.89,中文,,0,0,0,,要祝贺你新婚快乐\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Felicitations and congratulations on your recent marriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.87,0:45:43.38,中文,,0,0,0,,虽然我并不特别在意\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Though I don't particularly care
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.38,0:45:46.38,中文,,0,0,0,,你把自己当英格兰人还是苏格兰人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}whether you consider yourself an Englishwoman or a Scot...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.55,0:45:50.67,中文,,0,0,0,,而且很显然 两者都不是\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}and apparently, neither do you.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.99,0:45:52.90,中文,,0,0,0,,你还戴着你原来的婚戒\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You still wear your old wedding ring?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.88,0:45:58.67,中文,,0,0,0,,情感的寄托而已\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Sentimental attachment.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.15,0:46:01.65,中文,,0,0,0,,我很怀疑你心中还有没有情感\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I doubt you have a sentimental bone in your body.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.19,0:46:08.99,中文,,0,0,0,,不过更有意思的问题是\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}But the more interesting question is
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.99,0:46:12.31,中文,,0,0,0,,为什么杜戈尔 麦肯齐会如此珍视你\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}why would Dougal MacKenzie consider you of such value,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.31,0:46:14.04,中文,,0,0,0,,竟收留你把你当自己人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}that he would rather adopt you as one of his own
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.04,0:46:15.54,中文,,0,0,0,,却不容许我质疑你\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}than allow me to question you?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.04,0:46:20.19,中文,,0,0,0,,我根本不知道你在说些什么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I am sure I have no idea what you're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.01,0:46:21.77,中文,,0,0,0,,真的吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.47,0:46:25.04,中文,,0,0,0,,敬国王\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}The king.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.41,0:46:27.11,中文,,0,0,0,,敬国王\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}The king.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.22,0:46:34.96,中文,,0,0,0,,我很高兴地听到 你还把国王当做君主\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I'm glad to hear that you still consider him your sovereign.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.96,0:46:37.42,中文,,0,0,0,,我们麦肯齐家族忠诚不渝\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}We MacKenzies are all loyal subjects.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.57,0:46:41.26,中文,,0,0,0,,这是我整一星期以来\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}That is the single most amusing thing
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.26,0:46:42.43,中文,,0,0,0,,听到的唯一一件好笑的事情\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I've heard all week.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.80,0:46:46.08,中文,,0,0,0,,我可以以为鞭笞那些无辜的犯人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}So I take it you haven't been amusing yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.08,0:46:48.29,中文,,0,0,0,,并没能逗乐你\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}by flogging some innocent prisoners then?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.29,0:46:49.73,中文,,0,0,0,,逗乐我\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Amusing myself?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.15,0:46:52.37,中文,,0,0,0,,说起来真是怪怪的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}What an odd thing to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.38,0:46:57.03,中文,,0,0,0,,从我们过去的会面来看 你是知道的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}As you know from our previous meeting,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.03,0:46:59.21,中文,,0,0,0,,我确确实实把惩罚看作是很严肃的事\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I consider flogging a very serious matter indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.06,0:47:27.86,中文,,0,0,0,,夫人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Madam,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.08,0:47:31.80,中文,,0,0,0,,你要了解你现在的处境\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}you need to understand your position.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.47,0:47:34.43,中文,,0,0,0,,此时此刻 我们第三次交锋\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}In this hour, our third encounter,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.86,0:47:39.70,中文,,0,0,0,,我十分希望即使采取任何必要手段\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I fully intend by any means necessary
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.70,0:47:41.74,中文,,0,0,0,,揭开你的本性\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}to discover both your true nature
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.48,0:47:44.09,中文,,0,0,0,,还有你掩藏的秘密\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}and the secrets that you hold.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.08,0:47:51.77,中文,,0,0,0,,也许你该问问桑德林罕姆公爵\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Perhaps you should ask the Duke of Sandringham.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.44,0:47:57.45,中文,,0,0,0,,哦 我的天呀\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Oh, dear me,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.50,0:48:00.34,中文,,0,0,0,,我希望不会留下污迹\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I do hope that won't stain.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.53,0:48:10.42,中文,,0,0,0,,虽然是棋行险招\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}A dangerous gambit to be sure,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.97,0:48:13.38,中文,,0,0,0,,但他的反应告诉我 弗兰克和教士的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}but his reaction told me that Frank and the Reverend
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.38,0:48:15.44,中文,,0,0,0,,推测是正确的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}were right in their speculation.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.44,0:48:18.62,中文,,0,0,0,,我怀疑你的祖先有一个庇护人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I suspect your ancestor had a patron,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.62,0:48:21.43,中文,,0,0,0,,一个非凡强大的人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}a prominent and powerful man who could protect him
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.43,0:48:23.13,中文,,0,0,0,,来庇护他 不受来自他上级的责难\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}from the censure of his superiors.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.13,0:48:26.31,中文,,0,0,0,,有可能是那个时代非常高层的人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Possibly, but it would have to have been someone very high up
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.31,0:48:28.92,中文,,0,0,0,,才能施加如此巨大的影响\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}in the hierarchy of the day to exert that kind of influence.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.44,0:48:30.95,中文,,0,0,0,,桑德林罕姆公爵\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}The Duke of Sandringham?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.85,0:48:33.59,中文,,0,0,0,,桑德林罕姆公爵\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}The Duke of Sandringham?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.94,0:48:37.35,中文,,0,0,0,,黑杰克能够在高地\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Black Jack was able to commit his various crimes
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.35,0:48:38.30,中文,,0,0,0,,犯下如此残酷的罪行\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}in the highlands
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.30,0:48:41.17,中文,,0,0,0,,就是因为他被一个位高权重的人所庇护着\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}because he was being protected by a powerful man,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.45,0:48:43.42,中文,,0,0,0,,这种庇护的代价\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}and the cost of such protection
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.42,0:48:46.10,中文,,0,0,0,,通常就是沉默和忠诚\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}was always silence and fidelity.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.74,0:48:50.04,中文,,0,0,0,,关于公爵你都知道些什么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}What do you know of the Duke?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.32,0:48:56.64,中文,,0,0,0,,真的吗 上尉 你非得这么迟钝不可吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Really, captain, must you be so obtuse?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.68,0:48:59.50,中文,,0,0,0,,到现在还不清楚吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Is it not clear by now
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.50,0:49:01.08,中文,,0,0,0,,你和我都在一个伟大而\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}that you and I are both in the employ
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.09,0:49:03.44,中文,,0,0,0,,权重的人的庇护之下吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}of the same great and powerful man?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.67,0:49:08.85,中文,,0,0,0,,不可能的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}That is impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.42,0:49:10.52,中文,,0,0,0,,他会跟我说的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}He would've told me.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.37,0:49:15.65,中文,,0,0,0,,因为他会把所有秘密都告诉你吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Because he tells you all his secrets?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.55,0:49:21.45,中文,,0,0,0,,你对他来说一定是以为非常特别的军官\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You must be a very special officer indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.41,0:49:27.90,中文,,0,0,0,,我只要派个信使去桑德林罕姆问问他就可以了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I will simply send a message to Sandringham asking him.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.37,0:49:32.82,中文,,0,0,0,,好主意\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Excellent idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.18,0:49:37.31,中文,,0,0,0,,我敢肯定 他看到你如此敏锐地\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I'm sure he'll be most pleased at your skill and acumen
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.31,0:49:39.18,中文,,0,0,0,,察觉到我的真实身份的时候 一定会很开心的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}at uncovering my identity,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.48,0:49:41.25,中文,,0,0,0,,或者\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}or...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.43,0:49:44.15,中文,,0,0,0,,公爵并不会赞赏你\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}perhaps your disruption of the Duke's
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.15,0:49:47.06,中文,,0,0,0,,去打搅他精心布下的局\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}carefully laid plans will not be rewarded.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.69,0:49:49.75,中文,,0,0,0,,也许他会不高兴\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Perhaps he will be displeased,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.75,0:49:53.03,中文,,0,0,0,,从而考虑结束你们之间的特殊关系\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}and take measures to terminate your special relationship,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.81,0:49:56.49,中文,,0,0,0,,收回对你惯有的庇护\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}withdraw the protection to which you've become accustomed,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.49,0:49:57.75,中文,,0,0,0,,这样好让你的上级军官\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}and thus leave you at the mercy
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.75,0:50:01.27,中文,,0,0,0,,还有当地的土豪 来好好疼爱你\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}of your superior officers and local authorities.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.87,0:50:05.98,中文,,0,0,0,,当然 最明智的行为\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}No, the wisest course of action
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.52,0:50:08.77,中文,,0,0,0,,就是让我继续我的任务\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}would be to allow me to continue my mission
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.34,0:50:12.86,中文,,0,0,0,,我不会向公爵提到\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}and give the Duke no indication of how close you came
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.65,0:50:16.33,中文,,0,0,0,,你差点就破坏了他为了王国所付出的心血\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}to disrupting his efforts on behalf of the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.22,0:50:33.33,中文,,0,0,0,,当然你是说 他的 呃 他夫人的心血\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You mean, of course, his, uh, his wife's efforts.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.19,0:50:36.05,中文,,0,0,0,,他夫人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}His wife?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.05,0:50:38.09,中文,,0,0,0,,公爵夫人 你见过她了吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}The duchess. You've met her?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.85,0:50:40.15,中文,,0,0,0,,哦 我一直没能有那个荣幸\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Oh, I've never had the pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.15,0:50:40.69,中文,,0,0,0,,真的吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.35,0:50:45.16,中文,,0,0,0,,公爵的代理人 就是公爵夫人的代理人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}An agent of the Duke is an agent of the duchess.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.85,0:50:48.11,中文,,0,0,0,,当然 我们一直有联系\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Well, we have been in communication.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.11,0:50:49.45,中文,,0,0,0,,用书信联系\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Communication by letter?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.39,0:50:52.80,中文,,0,0,0,,- 信使 是的 - 和公爵夫人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}- By messenger, yes. - With the duchess?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.80,0:50:54.46,中文,,0,0,0,,我们说的就是她 不是吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}That's who we're talking about, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.46,0:50:55.25,中文,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.38,0:50:57.39,中文,,0,0,0,,正是\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}That is, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.10,0:51:00.58,中文,,0,0,0,,我们说的正是她\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}that is who we're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.22,0:51:03.32,中文,,0,0,0,,可是 当然 嗯\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}But, of course, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.21,0:51:07.95,中文,,0,0,0,,公爵从来没有结过婚\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}the duke has never been married.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.71,0:51:20.53,中文,,0,0,0,,下士\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Corporal.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.30,0:51:23.49,中文,,0,0,0,,对不起 夫人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I'm sorry, madam.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.73,0:51:36.27,中文,,0,0,0,,一位绅士怎么会在桌子里放绳索\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}What kind of gentleman keeps a rope at his desk?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.65,0:51:39.01,中文,,0,0,0,,一位时刻准备着的绅士 夫人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}A prepared one, madam.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.15,0:51:41.65,中文,,0,0,0,,你可以走了 霍金斯\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You can go, Hawkins.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.58,0:51:44.43,中文,,0,0,0,,还有 下士\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}And corporal,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.94,0:51:48.65,中文,,0,0,0,,别回来 不管你听到什么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}don't come back, no matter what you hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.94,0:51:51.87,中文,,0,0,0,,- 去吧 - 是\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}- Go. - Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.62,0:52:10.64,中文,,0,0,0,,救命 来人啊\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Help, somebody!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.50,0:52:13.97,中文,,0,0,0,,救救我\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Help me!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.85,0:52:20.64,中文,,0,0,0,,现在\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.44,0:52:29.84,中文,,0,0,0,,我觉得我们应该从你的名字开始 嗯\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I think we should begin with your name, hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.14,0:52:32.27,中文,,0,0,0,,你的真实姓名\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Your real name.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.67,0:52:33.47,中文,,0,0,0,,然后\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.38,0:52:39.13,中文,,0,0,0,,你可以告诉我你知道的所有事情\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}you can tell me everything that you know about...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.14,0:52:43.08,中文,,0,0,0,,杜戈尔 麦肯齐\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Dougal MacKenzie...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.99,0:52:46.07,中文,,0,0,0,,他的兄弟 科勒姆\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}his brother Colum...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.70,0:52:49.61,中文,,0,0,0,,那个 额\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}the, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.29,0:52:52.77,中文,,0,0,0,,詹姆斯党人叛乱\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}the Jacobite rebellion...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.19,0:52:57.69,中文,,0,0,0,,还有 最后\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}and finally,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.43,0:53:01.79,中文,,0,0,0,,桑德林罕姆公爵\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}the Duke of Sandringham.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.41,0:53:06.43,中文,,0,0,0,,你会后悔的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You are going to regret this.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.57,0:53:09.48,中文,,0,0,0,,我很怀疑\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I doubt it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.34,0:53:31.48,中文,,0,0,0,,这是啥\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}What have we here?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.98,0:53:33.95,中文,,0,0,0,,天啊天啊\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}My, my.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.21,0:53:36.90,中文,,0,0,0,,这位女士还有利爪呢\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}The lady has claws.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.04,0:53:39.03,中文,,0,0,0,,锋利吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Are they sharp?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.94,0:53:46.00,中文,,0,0,0,,嗯 锋利吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Hmm, are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.28,0:53:54.70,中文,,0,0,0,,把手从我妻子身上拿开 我先谢谢您\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I'll thank ye to take your hands off my wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.24,0:53:57.65,中文,,0,0,0,,嘿 天哪\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Good god.
